	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f10246660982764>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10246660982764>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10246660982764>RE: zones?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10246660982764#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 21st 9:28 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=69206><span id= >dimle</span></a><br><span id=notbold>50 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.49]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The best place to port is where 1) there are lots of people, who have 2) enough money to pay for ports, and, ideally, where 3) not many 29+ level druids hang out..<br><br>WC has lots and lots of people, and is often a nexus for travellers in many different direcitions, so it is always good for ports. It usually has lots of druids hanging around porting, but there is usually enough business to go around.&nbsp;&nbsp;On servers where GFay is the trading zone, I would assume that would take the place of WC.<br><br>A great place is Lake of Ill Omen.  The players have enough money, and there is not much reason for high level druids to hang around there.  It has the side benefit of giving you some solo targets to fight while you wait for ports, up until level 33 or so.<br><br>Once you get high enough to go to the Dreadlands, binding there at the northwall can get your rich off ports --- lots of players, including rich higher levels from KC, need ports there.<br><br>It seems like the best times for ports are between 5:30 and 7:30 Eastern US time.  Many people when they log on after dinner are looking for a port to the place they plan to fight that night.  I often port until 7:30 or 8:00, then go look for a  place to level.<br><br>Personally, I charge a flat 20 pp to port, charge nothing to anyone below level 12, and don't accept tips.  You get more money I think by just porting for donations, but getting stiffed by higher level characters made me so bummed out, it was just better for me mentally to charge a higher fee up front.  I get Very few people who turn me down for my price being too high.  If they do, well *shrug* there are plenty of people who will pay the 20.<br><br>You can make money in other zones, too, but the steadiest money for porters seems to come from these three zones on my server.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
