	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102466351378678>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102466351378678>RE: zones?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102466351378678#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 21st 8:54 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117530><span id=Guru>Calabar</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>214 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I thought I’d do a lot of porting once I got my group ports, but thus far I really haven’t.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is mainly due to playing two different characters and having so many other things to do in game, such as craft skills.  So I can’t give you a lot of examples.  However, I can help a bit.  Great Divide is a good spot for ports.  Make you way there, you can get there from the Nexus, and bind yourself in the dwarf city.  Then gate in from time to time and either listen for ports or offer them both in city and in the zone outside.  I’ve been battling giants and dire wolves there with both my characters and I’ve seen people offer 50 and 100 plats for ports, though they are hardly the norm.  Another good spot would be Dread Lands, by the castle wall.  The run is rather scary from the druid ring, but if you can get someone to lead you and then bind yourself you’ll be in a good position to offer ports.  <br><br>However, be prepared to miss out on a lot of ports at 29.  I’ve found that those offering the most money for ports are heading TO places like GD and DL, which you won’t have group ports to yet.  Still, if you wish to make some coins this way, you shouldn’t have too much trouble doing so.  I just hit 34 this morning.  So who knows, maybe I’ll actually start doing some porting myself.  *smiles*  <br></p>&nbsp;<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 62nd Season<br><b>Jondor</b><br>Barbarian Beastlord, 54th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b> </td></tr>
