	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117530><span id=Guru>Calabar</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>214 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I’m doing the same thing you are, trying to find wisdom items that I can quest for myself.&nbsp;&nbsp;I got the Testament of Vanear so I too passed up on the shield.  However, I’d suggest you take a look at the quest for the Paw of Opolla.  I did most of this quest myself as a 33 druid.  The item can be held in either hand and has the following stats:  AC: +9 Sta: +5 Agi: +9 Wis: +9 Cha: -5 Disease Resist: -5 Mana: +5.  The quest is not overly involved and very doable.  Though it can also be very time consuming.  You’ll have to camp the Mutant Fungus in upper Guk, which I did with my 42 ranger, but with maps and your higher level camo, you should be able to reach the spot and camp the mutant.  Look up both the item and the quest on this sight.  You’ll find a very good walkthrough posted, I think, under the quest.  Its step by step and extremely helpful.  <br><br>Buying items is perfectly fine, but I have to tell you I’m most proud of the two hand held items I quested for myself.  <br></p>&nbsp;<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 62nd Season<br><b>Jondor</b><br>Barbarian Beastlord, 54th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b> </td></tr>
