	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10235817933248>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10235817933248>Zels</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10235817933248#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jun 8th 8:24 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=19880><span id= >randumb</span></a><br><span id=notbold>2 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have found that soloing Large Zelniaks in Dawnshroud is great exp. I started soloing them around lvl 37 or 38. I start out snaring one then charming it. Find another one and snare it and send your pet into attack. Always remember to snare your pet and the mob you are attacking. That way if charm breaks you can just run away.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Let your pet get down to half health and then cast fear on the mob. You can then go attack it or just sit and med for a while. If charm breaks you can just run back a little and recharm or if LOM you can just zone. The only things you have to worry about are those pesky lightcrawlers. If you keep your volume turned up you can hear them coming and you will have enough time to move out of the way.<br>  Every once in a while a wolf will aggro but if you are far enough away he will aggro on the mob your pet is attacking and not you or your pet. Just snare and fear the wolf and finish off the zel and wait for the wolf to come back.<br> At lvl 38 I was getting half a blue from each Zel I killed. I could usually kill 3 or 4 using one charmed pet. Some are still blue to me at lvl 44 but it takes quite a few more to get the same ammont of exp.<br><br>Raaka<br>44 Druid &lt;Order of the Ardent&gt;</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
