	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=69206><span id= >dimle</span></a><br><span id=notbold>50 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.49]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Your best bet, really, is to learn to quad kite.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you have a wisdom over 150 it should be easy, and the ideal place to learn is in IC on the snow cougars.  Read the descriptions on how to do it located elsewhere in this discussion, then start out doing just two at a time until you get the hang of it.  Pull them down to near the gnome pirate outpost.<br><br>I, too, just hated the idea of quad kiting.  What it is, it really just takes getting used to it. It is not as safe as root dotting, of course.  But once you get the hang of it, you will find it doable.  And you will be getting experience three times or more faster than straight soloing.  THAT is worth figuring out how to do it.<br><br>Getting them rounded up and close together is pretty easy; just run around them in a circle a couple of times, then back away from them in a straight line.<br><br>I realize you don't want to quad kite, but if you don't, you are missing out on a way to level, in my opinion, faster than any other class in the game except for quadkiting wizzes.<br><br>Pulling to the bridge in EW is safe and reliable.  But quad kiting is the superhighway to level 44.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
