	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102345872056424>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102345872056424>RE: what to get......</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102345872056424#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 7th 10:16 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117530><span id=Guru>Calabar</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>214 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>It’s been a while, but I think studded leather is about the best armor you’ll be able to afford for a while unless you just get lucky.&nbsp;&nbsp;You might also look into getting a decent weapon.  The choices here can be hard. I started out with a scimitar because that’s what our epic will be.  But there are a lot more 1H blunt weapon choices out there for druids than 1H slashing.  And at level 20 I was giving an extremely good 2H blunt weapon so that’s what I’m best with at the moment.  Though it’s a very good idea to keep all your weapon skills maxed, as you never know what kind of weapon you may happen upon, its difficult to do.  I believe my skills are something like; 1H blunt – 15, 1H slash – 75, 2H blunt – 128.  But for a druid, weapon skills eventually become much less important.  Your real power will come from your spells.  At 31, my druid is just now starting to hang up is staff.  I still use it for killing most greens and I also like to fear kite with it while soloing, but wisdom is becoming more and more important.  <br><br>My advice is to try to get hold of a magic weapon of some sort, so you’ll be able to hit wisps, ghouls and other creatures that can only be hit by magic.  This site has a very good database of weapons.  On the left side of the page, look for Equipment and under that click By Slot.  Click on the weapon type you wish to use, such as 1 Hand Blunt.  Under Narrow by Class, select druid and click the reload button.  If the order is still set to ratio, you should new see the worst weapons on the top of the list and the best weapons on the bottom.  Click on a few of these to get an idea of how the pages are laid out.  What you want is a weapon that has magic listed under its name.  You’ll also see an average price listed. This is a very general price, but it gives you some idea of its value.  You can use this information to try to buy a specific weapon, which really comes in handy later.  Or you could turn on your auction channel and see what people are selling. You could even auction that you’re looking for a low level magical druid weapon.  Most mid or higher level players should be willing to cut you a deal if they have something they want to get rid of, as a few gold aren’t as precious by then.<br><br>You should also keep in mind that you’ll need money for spells.  Druids get a lot of spells and they don’t come cheap.  So you might not want to blow everything in one big shopping spree.  *grins*  <br><br>Good luck,<br></p>&nbsp;<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 62nd Season<br><b>Jondor</b><br>Barbarian Beastlord, 54th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b> </td></tr>
