	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10236395136141>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10236395136141>RE: what to get......</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=10236395136141#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jun 9th 12:26 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=166643><span id=Scholar>tamarask</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>53 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.25]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I used a Staff of the Observers at that level I believe. Good magic weapon. I was worried at the time about getting a scimmy as my epic is a 1hs, but now in hindsight, weapon skills are really useless. As you progress in level, you won't be hitting anything. Our spells are our damage dealers, we're casters after all. I suggest, instead of getting any weapon, you fill your hands with Wisdom items. And your armor too. What you need is mana, not a fast weapon. Get any and all armor pieces you can afford with a Wisdom bonus. 74p isn't enough for a Charred Guardian Shield, but you should look towards getting one of those. Perhaps you'll get lucky if you're guilded or have some high level buddies who will give it to you. After level 40, I carried a Paw of Opalla in my main hand and a CGS in the other. That gave me +18 Wisdom for both. For your neck, get a Black Iron Medallion. Those should run around 25-50pp max. Now, at level 55 and with my Epic, I hit for 40, with a very occasional 60 thrown in. And my groups always laugh to see a 55 druid meleeing anything. ::grins:: As you get higher levels, you can get killed getting that close to a mob. So, I suggest you not worry about increasing your weapon skills and save your money for spells and wisdom items to increase your mana pool instead.<br><br>My two coppers.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
