	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f102329456538956>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102329456538956>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102329456538956>RE: Best newb spells?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102329456538956#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 5th 12:40 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=166643><span id=Scholar>tamarask</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>53 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>It's been a long time since I was level 9, but you have a lot of great spells by that level. <br><br>Light healing is obviously your healing spell. I would keep that memmed at all times.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Enduring Breath allows you to breathe under water and requires a fish scale to cast.  <br>Endure cold is your first cold resist, used to raise your resistance again cold based dd's from mobs. <br>Firefist increases your attack. At level 9 you are probably still meleeing, so I would cast that just prior to a fight. It's self only.  <br>Strength of Earth increases your strength.  Protection of Wood is your first group skin buff. It's the group version of Skin Like Wood. Both spells increase HP and AC.  <br>Ignite is a fire based DD. <br>Shield of Thistles is your first damage shield. Cast this on yourself and your tanks just prior to a fight. It's a battle buff, so it doesn't last very long. <br>Thistlecoat is the first of your self only skin buffs. Have this on at all times. It will give you a damage shield and a nice AC bonus.  Invisible to Animals is self explanatory. One note, pets are considered animals. So, don't cast this on a pet class PC or you will effectively delete their pet. Good for when you are medding and you don't want wandering rats and lions attacking you. <br>Starshine I considered worthless. It casts a ball of light about the power of a Greater Lightstone, self only, useful mainly to Human druids. Treeform gives you a regeneration effect, and incidentally cures most poisons. It also is a low level camouflage. If the mob is already aggroed, it won't do much good. But if you are low on hp, and need to med, Treeform is very handy. You can't cast in a zone with no trees and if you die in tree form, your corpse will remain a tree. Makes it difficult in a corpse retrieval. <br><br>EQ Druids is a great site for your spell list. I suggest you look up some of your spells there and it will give you details as to what each one does.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
