	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102332751244225>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102332751244225>RE: Druid mistake plz help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=8&mid=102332751244225#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 5th 9:49 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73409><span id=Scholar>Mistress ancarett</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>108 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, don't give up entirely on your character if you're already hunting with an established group of friends or you don't have a way to pass your current equipment over to the new character (twinking, heh!).<br><br>I know more than a few level 50 plus druids who never put a point into wisdom when they created their characters. It doesn't have to be a killer statistic IF you equip creatively and work steadily towards your goal.<br><br>Research some inexpensive wisdom and mana gear: splitpaw gloves and jasper jewelry (silver jasper rings, electrum jasper earrings -- cheap and give wisdom) are a great start. When you reach level 19 you can start to make money doing some of the port-about quests (gem inlaid gauntlets, anyone?).<br><br>One advantage with your character, unless you put your extra points into intelligence, they all can bear fruit someday with your character: increased base strength is better carrying (and hitting) capacity, better stamina means more hitpoints, agility and dexterity contribute to hitting and dodging (respectively) in combat, even charisma helps with better merchant prices and increased chance to charm animal pets.<br><br>So remake if you want to, but don't feel you have to do so! Good luck.</p>&nbsp;<br>-- Ancarett, who lives at <a href="http://ancarett.com" target=_new>http://ancarett.com</a></td></tr>
